title: Esophageal cancer cases in England 2017 , by age and gender
summary: This grouped bar chart represents New registrations on the Y-axis. And, its value throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women.
All through the Months, similar trend was observed for Women and Men. In both cases, the New registrations have increased.
For Month 70-74, Men had the highest New registrations 1037.0 among the 2 groups and in 20-24, Women had the lowest New registrations 1.0.
Month 70-74 and 20-24 had the biggest gap of 371.0 between the highest and lowest New registrations found for Women.
min_summary: This is a grouped bar chart showing New registrations on the Y-axis throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women on the X-axis.
Over the 15 Months, the New registrations for both Women and Men have increased.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents New registrations on the Y-axis. And, how the value changed throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women.
All through the Months, similar trend was observed for Women and Men. In both cases, the New registrations have increased.
Out of all 2 groups, Men had the highest New registrations for Month 70-74 and Women had the lowest New registrations for Month 20-24.
For Month 70-74, Women had the highest New registrations among all 15 Months and it has the lowest New registrations in Month 20-24.
Month 70-74 and 20-24 had the biggest gap of 371.0 between the highest and lowest New registrations found for Women.
Among the groups, Men had the biggest difference in New registrations. Where the maximum New registrations was 259.25 times larger than the minimum New registrations.
On average, the Month 70-74 had the highest New registrations for all 2 groups Men, and Women. Whereas 20-24 had the lowest average New registrations.
